The process was supposed to have been done months ago, raising concerns about policy uncertainty in the industry. JOHANNESBURG - The Cabinet said on Thursday it has approved for publication a review of revisions to its charter for the mining sector, a process that was supposed to have been done months ago raising concerns about policy uncertainty in the industry.&quot;Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane will provide a briefing once the charter has been gazetted,&quot; the Cabinet said in a statement, without providing further details such as when it will be published.